@crashzzyla: the message is human are more resilience than you think. Many doujins end with  "the girl is broken, she is ruined". However human can grow, learn and start anew. Scar can heal, nightmare can be forgotten, your life is not over. You can find your own happiness as long as you continue to live. 

So do not give up on yourselves.  

Coincidentally, today is National Suicide Prevention Day, to people who are being suffocated by the darkness, the loneliness, the weight of responsibility, or the sadness similar to this girl.

Failure is always an option.

Let's say that you get up, and walk away. Quit your job, walk away from your family, and just let everything burn. Absolutely everyone involved is still better off than if you died. All of the things that you think would be made better by you dying will be made just as much better, if not more so, by you simple walking away. And you can always walk back, you can reconnect with people, and there will be a happy ending for you.
